              <img src="/images/lukas-hero.webp" alt="Lukáš Kmoch" class="hero-photo" width="864" height="1232" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- About -->
      <section id="about" class="section">
        <div class="section-label reveal">
          <span class="label-number">01</span>
          <span class="label-text">About</span>
        </div>
        <div class="about-grid">
          <div class="about-lead reveal" style="--delay: 0.1s">
            <p><span class="drop-cap">H</span>i, I'm Lukáš. At my core, I'm a <strong>.NET developer</strong> with a deep understanding of scalable application architecture. I've helped build the backend and frontend for 10+ companies including <em>Prazdroj, TSSK, Nakit, Lightverse, Dokempu, Campiri, Propeller, Freeway, Yacht Smart, and Skoda</em>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="about-body reveal" style="--delay: 0.2s">
            <p>I have deep experience building .NET MVC apps, Razor pages, and robust APIs. My deepest expertise lies in my 15 years of backend architecture experience, but I've deliberately expanded toward the frontend—initially exploring Vue a few years ago before shifting my full focus to React. While frontend certainly isn't my main strength, I know enough to comfortably navigate modern UI code. By combining this knowledge with AI tooling, I can expertly review, verify, and orchestrate frontend generation. This allows me to confidently build and validate full-stack solutions end-to-end, without shifting focus away from my core backend strengths.</p>
            <p>I'm a tech enthusiast who loves both learning and teaching. For over 5 years, I led .NET and web development courses at <strong>Gopas</strong>, helping corporate teams level up their engineering skills. Today, I share my learnings entirely in the open — posting regularly on LinkedIn and experimenting deeply with AI applications, Claude Code agents, custom rules, and AI skills.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Experience -->
